definition: ox/cow/bull/CL:條|条[tiao2],頭|头[tou2]/newton (abbr. for 牛頓|牛顿[niu2 dun4])/(slang) awesome

sentences.english: Otis asked, and turned to see three dizzy bullfrogs. 'Well, of course I did!
sentences.chinese: 奧蒂斯問道，並轉身看着三隻暈乎乎的牛蛙。

sentences.english: Someone likened his voice to the croaking of a bull-frog.
sentences.chinese: 有人把他的聲音比作牛蛙的叫聲。

sentences.english: A big bunch of bullfrog eggs float in the pond.
sentences.chinese: 一大堆牛蛙的卵在池塘上。

sentences.english: Splash! A big-eyed, bulging bullfrog plops into a pond.
sentences.chinese: “撲通”，一隻眼睛又大又突的牛蛙跳進池塘裏。

sentences.english: It is not suggested for use on Sickles, Bullfrogs and other tier 1 units.
sentences.chinese: 不推薦用在鐮刀，牛蛙和其他1級單位上。

sentences.english: The nutrient composition in the whole body of Rana catesbiana at different growth and developmental stages after overwintering was analysed.
sentences.chinese: 對越冬後牛蛙各生育階段的整體營養成份進行了分析。

sentences.english: Finally, the holograms were obtained with the bullfrog eyeballs as the object.
sentences.chinese: 最後生物實體以牛蛙眼球作目標，得到了全息圖。

sentences.english: A bullfrog is chock-full of hyperlife.
sentences.chinese: 一隻牛蛙充滿了超生命。

sentences.english: The diet composition of primary preys of bullfrogs was significantly different among different islands.
sentences.chinese: 不同島嶼上的牛蛙在主要食物類型構成上存在差異。

sentences.english: The noise in the zoo turned out to be the croaks of bullfrogs.
sentences.chinese: 動物園裏喧噪得很，原來是一羣牛蛙在叫。

sentences.english: A mouse looks out from the jaws of a huge voracious African bullfrog.
sentences.chinese: 一隻老鼠從一隻貪婪的非洲大牛蛙的巨口裏向外張望。

sentences.english: These frogs can jump 12-feet and have tooth.
sentences.chinese: 據悉，這些牛蛙能躍至三米高空，且長有牙齒。

sentences.english: This frog's eardrums are as big as her eyes.
sentences.chinese: 這隻牛蛙的耳鼓膜和眼睛一樣大。

sentences.english: If you bother the cottontails or bullfrogs, you will be fined.
sentences.chinese: 如果你干擾到白尾灰兔或牛蛙，你將受罰。

definition: Sichuan poached sliced fish in hot chili oil
duck's blood and beef tripe in spicy soup
fish head/fig. upright and unwilling to compromise
